               <msContents>
                  <summary>Mahzor according to the French rite, for the Three Pilgrimage Festivals</summary>
                  <msItem>
                     <title type="desc" xml:lang="he">מחזור מנהג צרפת לשלש רגלים</title>
                     <title type="desc" xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Maḥzor minhag Tsarfat le-shalosh reglaim</title>
                     <textLang mainLang="he">Hebrew</textLang>
                     <note>Continuation of MS. Opp. 670 (Neubauer 1055).</note>
                  </msItem>                  
               </msContents>
               <physDesc>
                  <objectDesc form="codex">
                     <supportDesc>
                        <support>parchment</support>
                        <extent>ff. 78</extent>
                     </supportDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
                  <handDesc>
                     <summary>Italian semi-cursive scripts</summary>
                     <handNote>The original MS. (Opp. 670/Neubauer 1055 and Opp. 669/Neubauer 1056) was written by two scribes, and each copied on a different kind of parchment. 
                        One scribe copied fols. 1r-29r of the first volume (No. 1055) and the entire original second volume (No. 1056, <locus>fols. 1-62</locus>), and pointed out the name Moses (No. 1056, <locus>fols. 45v and 50r</locus>). 
                        The other hand copied fols. 36v-137r in the first volume (No. 1055). Later hands copied fols. 30r-35r (late 13th cent.), 
                        and fols. 137v-140v (two hands) in No. 1055, and <locus>fols. 63r-78v</locus> in No. 1056 (late 13th cent.).</handNote>
                  </handDesc>

